# Student Portal Rules

## Required Reading

Before making changes to the student portal or learning system, read **`docs/arbor-learning-system-spec.md`** — the single source of truth for:

- Learning path optimization algorithm
- Mini-clase (adaptive mastery) algorithm
- Prerequisite scan protocol and cooldown mechanism
- Spaced repetition (activity-based)
- Retest gating policy
- Score prediction and confidence rules
- Dashboard data contracts (DRY)
- Student feedback UX contracts
- Goals and objectives UX
- Implementation status checklist

## Key Contracts

- **All learning methodology rules live in the master spec.** If the spec says it, it must be implemented. If it's not in the spec, it doesn't get built.
- **Metrics must use the shared metrics service** (`web/lib/student/metricsService.ts`). No duplicate calculations across components.
- **Mastery metrics are scoped to goal-relevant atoms**, not all 229.
- **Diagnostic source must always be labeled** (short diagnostic vs full test).
- **The atom result panel must show lifecycle context** (prereq scan, cooldown, gap detection) — not just pass/fail.

## Landing Page Preview Sync

The landing page (`web/app/components/landing/`) contains **static mockups** of portal UI:

- `MasterySection.tsx` → `LearningPathPreview` mirrors the portal's `LearningPathSection.tsx` (axis badges, atom nodes, review items, "Comenzar mini-clase" CTA)
- `ProgressSection.tsx` → `ProgressCard` mirrors `DashboardSections.tsx` (mastered atoms, mastery %, PAES questions unlocked, score/target, mission ring)

**When changing these portal components, check that the landing page previews still match.** Key things that can drift: metric names, visual structure, terminology, axis labels, CTA copy.

## Database

All database changes go through drizzle. See `AGENTS.md` for the full protocol.
